description: Borrowed from Dutch trekschuit, from trekken (“pull”) + schuit (“boat”).

entries.meaning: A horse-drawn canal boat or riverboat, used to carry goods or passengers in the Netherlands.
examples: And thou, much plumper dame [...]: thee I call: of whom in a treckschuyte, in some Dutch canal, the fat Jufvrouw Gelt, impregnated by a jolly merchant of Amsterdam, was delivered [...].
